Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 22nd of January,2025
Introduction
Thank you for choosing AMASAMPO ("we," "our," "us"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our application [App Name] ("the App"), a platform for buying and selling items. By using the App, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
1. Information We Collect
We collect different types of personal information to provide, improve, and personalize your experience on the App. The information we collect includes:
- Personal Information: When you register an account, create a listing, or communicate with other users, we may collect your name, email address, phone number, and payment details (if applicable).
- Transaction Information: We collect details of transactions you make on the App, including product listings, purchase details, and communication history.
- Device and Usage Information: We automatically collect information about your device (e.g., IP address, operating system, device type) and usage data (e.g., actions you take on the App, time spent, pages visited).
- Location Information: If enabled, we may collect your location to help match you with local buyers and sellers.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your personal information for the following purposes:
- To provide, maintain, and improve the App’s functionality and features.
- To facilitate transactions, including communication between buyers and sellers.
- To personalize your experience and tailor content to your preferences.
- To send you notifications regarding your account, transactions, and App updates.
- To comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our terms of service.
- To protect the security and integrity of the App.
3. Sharing Your Information
We may share your personal information in the following situations:
- With Other Users: When you create a listing or interact with other users, some of your information, such as your username, listing details, and communication history, may be shared with other users.
- With Service Providers: We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who help us operate and improve the App, such as payment processors, hosting services, and analytics providers. These service providers are bound by confidentiality agreements.
- In Response to Legal Requests: We may disclose your information to law enforcement or other government authorities if required by law or in response to a legal request.
- In the Event of a Sale or Merger: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your personal information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
4. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law. When your account is deleted or you request the deletion of your data, we will remove your personal information from our systems, except as necessary for legal or regulatory purposes.
5. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:
- The right to access your personal data.
- The right to correct or update your personal information.
- The right to delete your personal information or restrict processing.
- The right to object to the processing of your data for certain purposes.
- The right to withdraw your consent, if applicable.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [support@ama-sampo.com].
6. Security
We take the security of your personal information seriously and implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect it from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience on the App, analyze usage patterns, and serve personalized content and advertisements. You can manage cookie preferences through your device settings or browser.
8. Children’s Privacy
The App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information.
9. International Data Transfers
If you are located outside of [Your Country], your personal information may be transferred to and processed in [Your Country] or other jurisdictions. By using the App, you consent to the transfer of your personal information to these locations.
10. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will post the updated policy on this page and update the "Effective Date" at the top. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any changes.
